<img class="aligncenter wp-image-1529311" src="https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/POLICE-MEN.jpg?resize=640%2C337&#038;ssl=1" alt="Police rescue 7 kidnapped people in Osun" width="640" height="337" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/POLICE-MEN.jpg?resize=300%2C158&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/POLICE-MEN.jpg?resize=58%2C30&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/POLICE-MEN.jpg?resize=260%2C137&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/POLICE-MEN.jpg?resize=200%2C105&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/POLICE-MEN.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> The Osun Police Command has rescued seven people kidnapped on the Ibokun-Osogbo Road on Tuesday. A statement made available to newsmen on Saturday in Osogbo by the police spokesperson, SP Yemisi Opalola, stated that the effort of the state Commissioner of Police and other security agencies led to the release of the kidnapped people. “The victims were released due to the pressure mounted on the abductors by the police and other security agencies. “The victims will soon be reunited with their families,’’ the statement said. The Commissioner of Police, Mr Olawale Olokode, appealed to residents to collaborate with the police to get rid of all criminal elements in Osun. He assured the public of their safety as security measures have been put in place to forestall future occurrence. The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports that gunmen blocked Ibokun-Osogbo Road in the Obokun Local Government Area on Tuesday evening, killing one person and kidnapping an unspecified number of travellers. [NAN] Vanguard News Nigeria Eight staff of Osun College of Technology, Esa-Oke were on Tuesday kidnapped by unidentified gunmen. December 5, 2018 In "News" There are strong indications that the abductors of the three officials of Osun State government, kidnapped in Kogi State, on Friday, may have established contact with their victims’ families. April 24, 2016 In "News" The Permanent Secretary of Osun State Ministry of Finance, Budget and Economic Planning, Mrs Adebimpe Ogunlumade has been abducted by gunme‎n while returning to Osogbo from Abuja. April 22, 2016 In "News"